\begin_layout Standard
Manjaro Linux packages are hosted on a number of servers across the world;
 these servers
\series bold
 mirror
\series default
 the official Manjaro software repository.
 When you first install Manjaro it will try to work out which server is
 closest to you so that software downloads complete as quickly as possible.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sometimes, though, the list of mirrors can get old.
 New mirrors can become available, and some mirrors are removed.
 Updates to Manjaro will regularly trigger an update of the mirror list,
 but sometimes it's useful to do this manually.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To update the mirror list use the following command:
\begin_inset Float marginfigure
wide false
sideways false
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename images/maintaining-your-system/pacman-mirrors.png
	lyxscale 50
	width 95col%

\end_inset


\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\family typewriter
sudo pacman-mirrors -g
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman-mirrors
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
pacman-mirrors
\end_layout

\end_inset

 -g
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This will test the speed of all currently available mirrors and set your
 machine to use the best for you.
 Once this command has completed, you should force a download of the package
 lists:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman -Syyu
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Choosing mirrors
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If you would like more control over which mirrors to use, run the command:
\begin_inset Float marginfigure
wide false
sideways false
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename images/maintaining-your-system/pacman-mirrors-i.png
	lyxscale 50
	width 95col%

\end_inset


\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\family typewriter
sudo pacman-mirrors -i
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman-mirrors -i
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This will allow you to select which mirror, or mirrors, to try when checking
 for software updates and downloading new packages.
 It's normally best to choose mirrors that are geographically close to you,
 so if you're in Canada then Canadian and US servers are generally a good
 bet.
 Of course, you're free to choose whichever you want!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To reset back to an automatic choice, run this command:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman-mirrors -g -c all
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Remember to force a download of the package lists to use the new mirrors!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Switching branches
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Switching branches
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
branches
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When you install Manjaro you will be using the stable branch.
 This set of packages has the most testing and so is the best for most users.
 However, you may want to help test packages before they move to the stable
 repository:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman-mirrors -g -b testing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The testing repository has packages that have been checked by the Manjaro
 development team to make sure they work correctly.
 However, the amount of testing done is much smaller than for the stable
 branch - but this is how they get tested!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If you want to live on the bleeding edge, you can switch to the unstable
 branch.
 This is normally used by the Manjaro developers.
 Packages from the unstable branch can cause problems, so this is not something
 to do lightly:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman-mirrors -g -b unstable
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After switching branches you will need to force an update of the package
 lists:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman -Syyu
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If you switch away from the stable branch, but want to move back, it's actually
 pretty easy:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman-mirrors -g -b stable
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This will leave the newer packages on your system and these will be replaced
 as the stable branch catches up.
 However, if you want to force a downgrade of packages back to the stable
 version, use:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote

\family typewriter
sudo pacman -Syyuu
\end_layout

